Aim
To control home appliances using ESP32 and Blynk application.
Requirements
• ESP32
• LED
• 220Ω Resistor
• Blynk App
• WiFi Connection
Procedure
Step 1: Circuit Connection
1. Open Wokwi/Tinkercad or use ESP32 hardware.
2. Connect LED to GPIO pin of ESP32.
3. Provide power supply to the circuit.
Step 2: Blynk Setup
1. Install Blynk IoT application.
2. Create a new template.
3. Select ESP32 and WiFi connection.
4. Copy the Authentication Token.
Step 3: Configure Datastream
1. Create Virtual Pin V0.
2. Add button widget in dashboard.
3. Save and apply settings.
Step 4: Arduino Programming
1. Open Arduino IDE.
2. Install ESP32 board package and Blynk library.
3. Write and upload the program.
Step 5: Execution
1. Start simulation/run hardware.
2. Control LED using Blynk app.
3. Observe ON/OFF operation.
Result
Thus, the simple home automation system using ESP32 and Blynk was implemented successfully.
